---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Refund Policy - UrbanBiome">
  <main class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="legal-header">
        <h1>Refund Policy</h1>
        <p>Last updated: January 2024</p>
      </header>

      <div class="legal-content">
        <section>
          <h2>30-Day Money-Back Guarantee</h2>
          <p>We stand behind the quality of Bristol Geospatial Explorer and offer a 30-day money-back guarantee for new subscribers.</p>
          <p>If you are not completely satisfied with our service within the first 30 days of your subscription, you may request a full refund of your initial payment.</p>
          <p>This guarantee applies only to first-time subscribers and covers the first month's subscription fee.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Refund Eligibility</h2>
          <p>You are eligible for a refund if:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>You request the refund within 30 days of your initial subscription</li>
            <li>This is your first subscription to Bristol Geospatial Explorer</li>
            <li>You have not previously received a refund from us</li>
            <li>Your account has not been terminated for violation of our Terms of Service</li>
          </ul>
          
          <p><strong>Note:</strong> Refunds are not available for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Subscription renewals (after the initial 30-day period)</li>
            <li>Partial months of service</li>
            <li>Accounts terminated for policy violations</li>
            <li>Services already consumed or downloaded data exports</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>How to Request a Refund</h2>
          <p>To request a refund, please contact our support team within 30 days of your initial subscription:</p>
          
          <div class="contact-box">
            <p><strong>Email:</strong> support@urbanbiome.co.uk</p>
            <p><strong>Subject:</strong> Refund Request - [Your Account Email]</p>
            <p><strong>Include:</strong> Your account email, subscription date, and reason for refund</p>
          </div>
          
          <p>Our support team will respond to your refund request within 2 business days. We may ask for additional information to process your request.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Refund Processing</h2>
          <p>Once your refund request is approved:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Your subscription will be cancelled immediately</li>
            <li>Access to the service will be terminated</li>
            <li>Refunds are processed through Paddle, our payment processor</li>
            <li>The refund will be credited to your original payment method</li>
            <li>Processing time is typically 5-10 business days</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Please note that it may take additional time for the refund to appear on your bank or credit card statement, depending on your financial institution.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Subscription Cancellation</h2>
          <p>You can cancel your subscription at any time without requesting a refund:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Log into your account and visit the billing section</li>
            <li>Click "Cancel Subscription"</li>
            <li>Your access will continue until the end of your current billing period</li>
            <li>No further charges will be made</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Cancelled subscriptions do not automatically qualify for refunds unless within the 30-day guarantee period.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Service Credits</h2>
          <p>In cases where a refund may not be applicable, we may offer service credits as an alternative resolution:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Extended service periods</li>
            <li>Additional features or capabilities</li>
            <li>Credit towards future subscriptions</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Service credits are offered at our discretion and may be provided in lieu of monetary refunds in certain circumstances.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Dispute Resolution</h2>
          <p>If you are not satisfied with our refund decision, you may:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Request escalation to our management team</li>
            <li>Contact Paddle directly regarding payment disputes</li>
            <li>File a chargeback with your credit card company (note: this may affect future service eligibility)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We encourage customers to work with us directly to resolve any issues before pursuing external dispute resolution.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Exceptions and Special Circumstances</h2>
          <p>We may consider refunds outside our standard policy in exceptional circumstances, such as:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Extended service outages affecting your ability to use the platform</li>
            <li>Significant service changes that materially affect functionality</li>
            <li>Billing errors or duplicate charges</li>
            <li>Technical issues preventing normal service use</li>
          </ul>
          <p>These situations are evaluated on a case-by-case basis and are subject to management approval.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Contact Information</h2>
          <p>For questions about refunds or to request a refund, please contact us:</p>
          
          <div class="contact-box">
            <p><strong>Email:</strong> support@urbanbiome.co.uk</p>
            <p><strong>Response Time:</strong> Within 2 business days</p>
            <p><strong>Business Hours:</strong> Monday-Friday, 9:00 AM - 5:00 PM GMT</p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="legal-footer">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="legal-links">
        <a href="/">Back to Home</a>
        <a href="/pricing">Pricing</a>
        <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    min-height: 100vh;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a1a 0%, #2d3748 100%);
    color: white;
    padding: 40px 20px;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }

  .legal-header h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    color: rgba(100, 200, 100, 1);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .legal-header p {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
  }

  .legal-content {
    background: rgba(25, 25, 25, 0.98);
    border: 1px solid rgba(100, 200, 100, 0.3);
    border-radius: 15px;
    padding: 40px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .legal-content section {
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .legal-content h2 {
    color: rgba(100, 200, 100, 1);
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .legal-content p {
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
  }

  .legal-content ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
  }

  .legal-content li {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
  }

  .contact-box {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(100, 200, 100, 0.2);
    margin: 20px 0;
  }

  .contact-box p {
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .contact-box p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .legal-footer {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 40px;
    padding-top: 30px;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  }

  .legal-links {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 20px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .legal-links a {
    color: rgba(100, 200, 100, 1);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
  }

  .legal-links a:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .legal-header h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }
    
    .legal-content {
      padding: 30px 20px;
    }
    
    .legal-links {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 15px;
    }
  }
</style>